$ SQL statement

An *SQL statement* is a text-string that conforms to grammar set forth in the → misc/ISO/9075[SQL standard].

Classes of SQL statements:
  • Schema statements
  • Data statements
  • Transaction statements
  • Control statements
  • Connection statements
  • Session statements
  • Diagnostic statements
  • Dynamic statements
  • Embedded exception statements

sa:

  The text of an SQL statement can be annotated with → development/databases/SQL/statement/comment[comments].

  In → Microsoft/dot-net, an SQL statement is represented by the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DbCommand[`System.Data.Common.DbCommand` class].

  In → development/databases/ADO[ADO DB], an SQL statement is represented by the → development/databases/ADO/objects/command[`ADODB.Command`] object.
  -
  In → development/databases/ADO[ADODB], an SQL statement can be executed with the → development/databases/ADO/objects/connection/execute[`execute()`] method that is found in the
  → development/databases/ADO/objects/connection[`ADODB.Connection`] object.
